forge.gui
Class MultiPhaseProgressMonitorWithETA

java.lang.Object
  net.slightlymagic.braids.util.progress_monitor.BaseProgressMonitor
      forge.gui.MultiPhaseProgressMonitorWithETA
All Implemented Interfaces:
BraidsProgressMonitor
public class MultiPhaseProgressMonitorWithETA
extends BaseProgressMonitor

GUI Progress Monitor that displays the ETA (Estimated Time of Arrival or completion) on some platforms and supports one or multiple phases of progress. In this implementation, each phase opens a new dialog.

public MultiPhaseProgressMonitorWithETA(String title,

                                        long totalUnitsFirstPhase,
                                        float minUIUpdateIntervalSec,
                                        float[] phaseWeights)
Create a GUI progress monitor and open its first dialog.

Parameters:
title - the title to give the dialog box(es)
numPhases - the total number of phases to expect
totalUnitsFirstPhase - the total number of units that will be processed in the first phase
minUIUpdateIntervalSec - the approximate interval at which to update the dialog box in seconds
phaseWeights - see BaseProgressMonitor
